15 SECTION 18. Article 9 of Chapter 25 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
16 a new section to read:
17 "§ 25-9-306.2. Law governing perfection and priority of security interests in controllable
18 accounts, controllable electronic records, and controllable payment intangibles.
19 (a) General Rules for Governing Law. – Except as provided in subsection (b) of this
20 section, the local law of the controllable electronic record's jurisdiction specified in
21 G.S. 25-12-107(c) and (d) governs perfection, the effect of perfection or nonperfection, and the
22 priority of a security interest in a controllable electronic record and a security interest in a
23 controllable account or controllable payment intangible evidenced by the controllable electronic
24 record.
