14 SECTION 75. G.S. 25-3-401 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 25-3-401. Signature.Signature necessary for liability on instrument.
16 (a) A person is not liable on an instrument unless (i) the person signed the instrument, or
17 (ii) the person is represented by an agent or representative who signed the instrument and the
18 signature is binding on the represented person under G.S. 25-3-402.
19 (b) A signature may be made (i) manually or by means of a device or machine, and (ii)
20 by the use of any name, including a trade or assumed name, or by a word, mark, or symbol
21 executed or adopted by a person with present intention to authenticate a writing."
22 SECTION 76. G.S. 25-3-604 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 25-3-604. Discharge by cancellation or renunciation.
24 (a) A person entitled to enforce an instrument, with or without consideration, may
25 discharge the obligation of a party to pay the instrument (i) by an intentional voluntary act, such
26 as surrender of the instrument to the party, destruction, mutilation, or cancellation of the
27 instrument, cancellation or striking out of the party's signature, or the addition of words to the
28 instrument indicating discharge, or (ii) by agreeing not to sue or otherwise renouncing rights
29 against the party by a signed writing. The obligation of a party to pay a check is not discharged
30 solely by destruction of the check in connection with a process in which information is extracted
31 from the check and an image of the check is made and, subsequently, the information and image
32 are transmitted for payment.
33 (b) Cancellation or striking out of an endorsement indorsement pursuant to subsection (a)
34 of this section does not affect the status and rights of a party derived from the indorsement."
